# midiin: transport messages (manual lines 148-161; outputs lines 357-361).
# START/CONTINUE set `running` high and fire the `start`/`continue` triggers;
# STOP sets `running` low and fires `stop`. With initialrunning default 2 (auto,
# line 330) and no note received yet, the circuit starts stopped. Transport
# triggers use the engine standard 10 ms trigger (tickrate 1000 -> 10 ticks).
tickrate 1000
patch <<<
[midiin]
    start    = O1
    stop     = O2
    continue = O3
    running  = O4
>>>
@0 expect O4 0
@2 midisend trs start
@2 expect O1 1
@2 expect O4 1
@12 expect O1 0
@20 midisend trs stop
@20 expect O2 1
@20 expect O4 0
@30 expect O2 0
@40 midisend trs continue
@40 expect O3 1
@40 expect O4 1
@50 expect O3 0
